Responsive & Adaptive Layout System
Screen Size Breakpoints
Class	Width	Typical Device	Layout Strategy
Compact	< 600dp	Phones (portrait)	Single column, bottom nav
Medium	600–840dp	Tablets (portrait), large phones	Single/two column, navigation rail
Expanded	> 840dp	Tablets (landscape), desktops	Two/three column, nav drawer
Folder Structure for Adaptive Layouts
res/
├── layout/                        ← Default (Compact — phones portrait)
│   └── fragment_[name].xml
├── layout-w600dp/                 ← Medium — tablet portrait / large phone
│   └── fragment_[name].xml        (two-column, navigation rail)
├── layout-w840dp/                 ← Expanded — tablet landscape
│   └── fragment_[name].xml        (three-column, nav drawer)
├── layout-land/                   ← Landscape override for phones
│   └── fragment_[name].xml
└── layout-w600dp-land/            ← Tablet landscape (if different from w840dp)
    └── fragment_[name].xml

Phone Layout (Compact — single column)
<!-- res/layout/fragment_[name].xml -->
<androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:paddingHorizontal="@dimen/screen_margin_horizontal">
    <!-- Single column content -->
</androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout>

Tablet Layout (Medium/Expanded — two column)
<!-- res/layout-w600dp/fragment_[name].xml -->
<androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent">
    <!-- Left panel -->
    <androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView
        android:id="@+id/panelLeft"
        android:layout_width="0dp"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:paddingHorizontal="@dimen/screen_margin_horizontal_large"
        app:layout_constraintStart_toStartOf="parent"
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toStartOf="@id/divider"
        app:layout_constraintWidth_percent="0.4">
        <!-- List or navigation content -->
    </androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView>
    <com.google.android.material.divider.MaterialDivider
        android:id="@+id/divider"
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        app:layout_constraintStart_toEndOf="@id/panelLeft"
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toStartOf="@id/panelRight" />
    <!-- Right panel -->
    <androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView
        android:id="@+id/panelRight"
        android:layout_width="0dp"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:paddingHorizontal="@dimen/screen_margin_horizontal_large"
        app:layout_constraintStart_toEndOf="@id/divider"
        app:layout_constraintEnd_toEndOf="parent">
        <!-- Detail content -->
    </androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView>
</androidx.constraintlayout.widget.ConstraintLayout>

Landscape Phone Layout
<!-- res/layout-land/fragment_[name].xml -->
<!-- Use horizontal ScrollView root or split the layout into two panes -->
<!-- Never let content overflow outside the screen in landscape -->
<androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent">
    <LinearLayout
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:orientation="horizontal"
        android:paddingHorizontal="@dimen/screen_margin_horizontal">
        <!-- Left content (40%) -->
        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="0dp"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_weight="0.4"
            android:orientation="vertical" />
        <!-- Right content (60%) -->
        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="0dp"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_weight="0.6"
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/spacing_16" />
    </LinearLayout>
</androidx.core.widget.NestedScrollView>

