Accessibility Standards
Every layout must satisfy these requirements. These are not optional.

Mandatory Rules
✓  Every ImageView that conveys information must have android:contentDescription
✓  Every ImageView that is decorative must have android:contentDescription="@null"
✓  Every clickable view must have android:contentDescription (if no visible text)
✓  android:clickable="true" and android:focusable="true" must appear together
✓  Minimum touch target: 48dp × 48dp (use android:minWidth / android:minHeight)
✓  Text contrast ratio: minimum 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text (≥18sp or ≥14sp bold)
✓  Group related elements with android:contentDescription on the container, and
   android:importantForAccessibility="no" on children
✓  Focusable elements appear in logical reading order (top→bottom, start→end)
✓  Use android:labelFor to link TextInputLayout labels to EditTexts
✓  Use android:hint on all text inputs — it becomes the TalkBack label
✓  Use android:nextFocusDown / nextFocusForward for keyboard/D-pad navigation
✓  All font sizes in sp (never dp for text)
✓  Layouts must not clip content at 200% font scale — use scrollable containers

Content Description Templates
<!-- Interactive element with visible text — no separate contentDescription needed -->
<com.google.android.material.button.MaterialButton
    android:text="@string/action_save"    <!-- TalkBack reads this automatically -->
    ... />
<!-- Icon-only button — contentDescription required -->
<ImageButton
    android:src="@drawable/ic_share_24"
    android:contentDescription="@string/cd_share_recording"
    android:minWidth="@dimen/touch_target_min"
    android:minHeight="@dimen/touch_target_min"
    ... />
<!-- Decorative image — suppress from TalkBack -->
<ImageView
    android:src="@drawable/illustration_empty"
    android:contentDescription="@null"
    android:importantForAccessibility="no"
    ... />
<!-- Grouped content — describe the container, suppress children -->
<LinearLayout
    android:contentDescription="@string/cd_recording_item_[title]_[duration]"
    android:clickable="true"
    android:focusable="true">
    <TextView android:importantForAccessibility="no" ... />
    <TextView android:importantForAccessibility="no" ... />
</LinearLayout>

Touch Target Padding (for small icons that must stay visually small)
<!-- Visual size: 24dp icon. Tap area: 48dp minimum -->
<ImageView
    android:layout_width="24dp"
    android:layout_height="24dp"
    android:padding="12dp"    <!-- adds 12dp on each side → 48dp tap target -->
    android:background="?attr/selectableItemBackgroundBorderless"
    ... />

RTL (Right-to-Left) Support
✓  Always use Start/End instead of Left/Right:
     android:layout_marginStart   not android:layout_marginLeft
     android:paddingStart         not android:paddingLeft
     app:layout_constraintStart   not app:layout_constraintLeft
     android:layout_gravity="start" not "left"
✓  Drawables that need mirroring: android:autoMirrored="true"
✓  No absolute positions (no translationX without RTL logic)
✓  Test every screen with developer options → Force RTL layout direction

Performance Rules
✓  Maximum view hierarchy depth: 5 levels
✓  Use ConstraintLayout to flatten hierarchies — replace nested LinearLayouts
✓  Use <include> for repeated layout sections (headers, footers, states)
✓  Use <merge> as root of included layouts to eliminate one level of nesting
✓  Use ViewStub for layouts that are rarely shown (error states, onboarding overlays)
✓  Use app:srcCompat for VectorDrawable in ImageView (not android:src for vectors)
✓  RecyclerView items must have fixed size where possible (setHasFixedSize = true)
✓  Never use wrap_content on RecyclerView height — always match_parent or fixed dp

ViewStub for rarely-shown states:

<ViewStub
    android:id="@+id/stubError"
    android:inflatedId="@+id/layoutError"
    android:layout="@layout/layout_error_state"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent" />

Merge tag for included layouts:

<!-- res/layout/layout_loading_state.xml -->
<merge xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    tools:parentTag="LinearLayout">
    <!-- Content inside merge — no extra wrapper View created on include -->
</merge>

Drawable Standards
Icon Usage
✓  All icons: VectorDrawable (@drawable/ic_[name]_[size].xml)
✓  Icon naming: ic_[semantic_name]_[size]dp.xml
     Examples: ic_add_24.xml, ic_delete_24.xml, ic_share_24.xml
✓  Use material.io/icons or the Google Fonts Material Symbols library
✓  Never embed bitmap icons — always vector
✓  Icon tint via app:tint="?attr/colorOnSurface" — never hardcoded color in vector
✓  Use android:tint on ImageView rather than modifying the drawable's fillColor

